definition.value: A synthetic 28-amino acid polypeptide consisting of glutaminyl, seryl, prolyl, seryl, tyrosyl, prolyl, alpha-aspartyl, arginyl, alpha-glutamyl, tyrosyl, seryl, alpha-aspartyl, alpha-glutamyl, alpha-aspartyl, arginyl, glutaminyl, isoleucyl, lysyl, glutaminyl, methionyl, leucyl, histidyl, glutaminyl, alpha-glutamyl, cysteinyl, prolyl, arginyl and leucinamide residues joined in sequence. A synthetic version of the peptide epitope from the major peanut allergen glycoprotein Arachis hypogaea h2 (Ara-h2).

A glycoside that is beta-D-xylose in which the hydrogen of the anomeric hydroxy group is replaced by a 4-aminobutyl group. A synthetic version of the beta-xylosyl glycoside (BXG) epitope from the major peanut allergen glycoprotein Arachis hypogaea h2 (Ara-h2).
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the four free amino groups of amikacin; major species at pH 7.3.
An  alkanethiol that is propane substituted by a sulfanyl group at position 2.
A beta-D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group is specified as tricosanoyl.
A  N-acyl-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the acyl group is specified as tricosanoyl.
A hydrochloride obtained by combining amiloride with one molar equivalent of hydrochloric acid.
A beta-D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group is specified as tetracosanoyl.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of amiloride.
A N-acyl-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the acyl group is (15Z)-tetracosenoyl.
An amino tetrasaccharide consisting of four N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked (1->2) throughout; forms the minimal structure for the A epitope of Brucella spp.
A N-acyl-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is hexacosanoyl.
A thiocarbonyl compound that is propanethial in which the sulfur atom carries an oxo group. It is a lachrymatory factor found in onions.
A beta-D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group is specified as (17Z)-hexacosenoyl.
A N-acyl-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is (17Z)-hexacosenoyl.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 16:1 in which the 1-acyl group is (9E)-hexadecenoyl.
A 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkenyl group is (1Z,9Z)-octadecadienyl.
A 2-deoxy-D-glucose that is D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been replaced by a hydrogen.
A D-hexopyranose 6-phosphate that is the 6-monophospho derivative of 2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphinganine in which the acyl group specified is hexadecanoyl.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is hexadecanoyl.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is octadecanoyl.
An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose 6-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is eicosanoyl.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is docosanoyl.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is tricosanoyl.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is tetracosanoyl.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is (15Z)-tetracosenoyl.
An amino disaccharide consisting of two N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked (1->3); forms the minimal structure for the M epitope of Brucella spp.
The monosaccharide sulfate that is N-acetylated 6-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucosamine linked glycosidically to a 3-aminopropyl group.
The organosulfate oxoanion that is N-acetylated 6-O-sulfonato-beta-D-glucosamine linked glycosidically to a 3-aminopropyl group.
A galactosiduronic acid in which beta-D-galacturonic acid is linked glycosidically to a 3-aminopropyl group.
A carbohydrate acid derivative anion in which the anionic species formed by proton loss from the carboxy function of beta-D-galacturonic acid is linked glycosidically to a 3-aminopropyl group.
Any N-nitro compound obtained by formal replacement of one or more of the hydrogens of a nitroguanidine by an organyl group.
Any nitroguanidine derivative resulting from the replacement of one or more hydrogens of 1-nitroguanidine by an organyl group.
Any nitroguanidine derivative resulting from the replacement of one or more hydrogens of 2-nitroguanidine by an organyl group.
The  organosulfate oxoanion formed by proton loss from the sulfate group of N-acetyl-6-O-sulfo-D-glucosamine.
The monosaccharide sulfate formed by sulfating D-glucosamine at O(6).
The organosulfate oxoanion formed by proton loss from the sulfate group of 6-O-sulfo-D-glucosamine.
An oligosaccharide sulfate formed by sulfating propyl N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-2-O-acetyl-alpha-D-glucoside at O-6 of the reducing-end residue.
The organosulfate oxoanion formed by deprotonation of the sulfo group in beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp2Ac6SOPr.
The phosphate ester of propanoic acid.
An oligosaccharide sulfate formed by sulfating methyl 6-O-sulfo-alpha-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->4)-6-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucopyranoside at O-6 of each glucose residue.
The organosulfate oxoanion formed by deprotonation of the sulfo groups in alpha-D-Glcp6S-(1->4)-beta-D-Glcp6SOMe.
A beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphinganine in which the acyl group specified is hexadecanoyl.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphinganine in which the acyl group specified is hexadecanoyl.

A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1-acyl group is specified as palmitoyl while the acyl group (R) at position 2 is octadecadienoyl with the two double bonds at unspecified positions.
A phosphatidylcholine 34:3 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and (6Z,9Z,12Z)-octadecatrienoyl (gamma-linolenoyl) respectively.
A phosphatidylethanol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1,2-dipalmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanol; major species at pH 7.3.
A trans,trans-2,3,4,5-tetradehydroacyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of trans,trans-2,4-hexadienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
